Deeply unsettling, as always - we often describe someone or something as having a method to their madness. We rarely see how that method is developed, and it's just as unpleasant as one might think, it seems. I am acutely reminded of SCP-5101 though it's something of an inversion - salvador is much warmer in his mannerisms than Attendant JL, and the mental damage suffered here is more like being pulled apart than being crushed. In any case, excellent work. +1







